<subSubSection pageId="0" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1535,1993]" pageId="0">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,373,1535,1560]" pageId="0">Description. Male:</emphasis>
Antennae: length 
<quantity box="[581,703,1536,1560]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.1" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="0" unit="mm" value="10.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="10.0">10–11 mm</quantity>
, slender, greyish inferiorly at base of club and white between the terminal club and the apiculus, as usual in most 
<emphasis box="[689,815,1573,1596]" italics="true" pageId="0">Notocrypta</emphasis>
species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1535,1993]" box="[199,1078,1607,1632]" pageId="0">Palpi: covered with dense scaling, dark brown superiorly and whitish laterally.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1535,1993]" box="[199,964,1644,1669]" pageId="0">Wings: ground colour dark brown, almost black, paler on underside.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1535,1993]" pageId="0">
Forewing: length 
<quantity box="[399,545,1679,1704]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.025" metricValueMax="2.1" metricValueMin="1.95" pageId="0" unit="mm" value="20.25" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="19.5">19.5–21 mm</quantity>
; white median band very wide, reaching the costal margin on the underside; in space 4 a white thin spot, 
<quantity box="[445,539,1716,1740]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="0" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 mm</quantity>
long, starting from the white band and projecting distally; white subapical dots in spaces 6 to 8 absent; in the basal area of the underside three evident linear patches of dark androconial scales, in spaces 1b, 2 and the cell (see 
<figureCitation box="[482,550,1788,1813]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1997,2019]" captionTargetBox="[208,1386,193,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[208,1386,193,1978]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 6. N. ariannae n. sp. male Paratype, underside. Scale 2: 1" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1040654/files/figure.png" pageId="0">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1535,1993]" box="[199,1318,1823,1848]" pageId="0">Hindwing: underside, three small whitish spots in the discal area, one in space 3 and two in space 4.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1535,1993]" pageId="0">
Genitalia: typical of the genus; uncus (
<figureCitation box="[631,697,1860,1885]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1091,1113]" captionText="FIGURE 3. N. ariannae n. sp. male Paratype genitalia, uncus dorsal view" pageId="0">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) with two long distal projections, as long as in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boisduval" baseAuthorityYear="1832" box="[1226,1389,1860,1884]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Notocrypta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="feisthamelii">
<emphasis box="[1226,1389,1860,1884]" italics="true" pageId="0">N. feisthamelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Felder &amp; Felder" authorityYear="1862" box="[184,345,1896,1920]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Notocrypta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curvifascia">
<emphasis box="[184,345,1896,1920]" italics="true" pageId="0">N. curvifascia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, longer than in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wood-Mason &amp; de Niceville" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[540,686,1896,1920]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Notocrypta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paralysos">
<emphasis box="[540,686,1896,1920]" italics="true" pageId="0">N. paralysos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; valva (
<figureCitation box="[785,857,1895,1920]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1743,1765]" captionText="FIGURE 4. N. ariannae n. sp. male Paratype genitalia, valva lateral view" pageId="0">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) wide, cullier (sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Reverdin" box="[1116,1294,1895,1920]" pageId="0" refString="Reverdin, J. L. (1910) Note sur l'armure genitale de quelques Hesperides palearctiques. Bulletin de la Societe botanique de Geneve, 2, 1 - 16" type="journal article" year="1910">Reverdin, 1910</bibRefCitation>
) with distal projection long, covered with large teeth and inner projection shorter.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1535,1993]" box="[199,400,1968,1993]" pageId="0">Female unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
