<paragraph blockId="5.[199,610,151,176]" box="[199,610,151,176]" pageId="5">Additional diagnostic characters are:</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,223,392]" pageId="5">
1) smaller than sympatric 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boisduval" baseAuthorityYear="1832" box="[461,624,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Notocrypta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="feisthamelii">
<emphasis box="[461,624,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="5">N. feisthamelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[639,707,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1963,1985]" captionTargetBox="[205,1411,977,1930]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[188,1412,962,1956]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 2. N. ariannae n. sp. male Holotype and three Paratypes, all from the type locality (row one and two), N. feisthamelii male, same locality and same date as above (row 3). Scale 1: 1" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1040650/files/figure.png" pageId="5">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) whose forewing length is 
<quantity box="[1012,1177,224,248]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.375" metricValueMax="2.43" metricValueMin="2.32" pageId="5" unit="mm" value="23.75" valueMax="24.3" valueMin="23.2">23.2–24.3 mm</quantity>
; 2) forewing white band wider and more rounded than in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boisduval" baseAuthorityYear="1832" box="[820,986,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Notocrypta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="feisthamelii">
<emphasis box="[820,986,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="5">N. feisthamelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Felder &amp; Felder" authorityYear="1862" box="[1075,1233,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Notocrypta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curvifascia">
<emphasis box="[1075,1233,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="5">N. curvifascia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, wider than in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Staudinger" baseAuthorityYear="1889" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Notocrypta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clavata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5">N. clavata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
;
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,223,392]" pageId="5">
3) forewing white subapical spots always absent (usually present or at least vestigial in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Felder &amp; Felder" authorityYear="1862" box="[1165,1324,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Notocrypta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curvifascia">
<emphasis box="[1165,1324,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="5">N. curvifascia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boisduval" baseAuthorityYear="1832" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Notocrypta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="feisthamelii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5">N. feisthamelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,439,968]" box="[199,1395,439,464]" pageId="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,439,464]" pageId="5">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is named after Arianna Chierici Bozano, granddaughter of the second author.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,439,968]" pageId="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,291,476,501]" pageId="5">Habitat</emphasis>
: All nine specimens of the new species have been found in a small isolated valley in the Xilin Mts., not far from the town of Huashuiwan in the Dayi County: noteworthy is the fact that they were sympatric with the congeneric 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boisduval" baseAuthorityYear="1832" box="[283,449,548,572]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Notocrypta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="feisthamelii">
<emphasis box="[283,449,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="5">N. feisthamelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. No other 
<emphasis box="[576,702,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="5">Notocrypta</emphasis>
specimen had been ever spotted before by the authors in many years of investigation of the butterfly fauna of 
<collectingRegion box="[684,774,583,608]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="5">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
and northern 
<collectingRegion box="[935,1020,584,607]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="5">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
Provinces. The collecting place was the valley bottom, between 
<date box="[472,644,620,645]" pageId="5" value="1200" valueMax="1400">
1200 and 
<quantity box="[588,644,620,644]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="5" unit="m" value="1400.0">1400</quantity>
</date>
m, in a mostly wooded environment (
<figureCitation box="[1091,1162,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1984,2006]" captionText="FIGURE 7. Type locality of N. ariannae" pageId="5">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
